         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is concerned with the problem of existence of monotone and/or convex splines, having degree $n$ and order of continuity $k$, which interpolate to a set of data at the knots. The interpolating splines are obtained by using Bernstein polynomials of suitable continuous piecewise linear functions; they satisfy the inequality $k \leqslant n - k$. The theorems presented here are useful in developing algorithms for the construction of shape-preserving splines interpolating arbitrary sets of data points. Earlier results of McAllister, Passow and Roulier can be deduced from those given in this paper.</p>
          </abstract>
